### AnkiConnect examples (use with REST client extensions or curl)

# Verify AnkiConnect
POST http://localhost:8765
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "version",
  "version": 6
}

### Ensure deck exists
POST http://localhost:8765
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "createDeck",
  "version": 6,
  "params": { "deck": "SuperAnki" }
}

### Add a basic note
POST http://localhost:8765
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "addNote",
  "version": 6,
  "params": {
    "note": {
      "deckName": "SuperAnki",
      "modelName": "Basic",
      "fields": {
        "Front": "abate",
        "Back": "to lessen; to reduce in degree\n\nExample: The storm finally abated."
      },
      "options": { "allowDuplicate": false },
      "tags": ["superanki", "source:BookTitle"]
    }
  }
}

